description:
&lt;p&gt;We have an excellent opportunity for an Endpoint &amp; Server Engineer to join our Server team at Hampshire Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust (HHFT). This post would suit an experienced desktop engineer or keen candidate wanting to move into an infrastructure role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The primary responsibility of the role is to manage the Trust’s Endpoint Protection, Management and Deployment Infrastructure to provide a secure &amp; optimised environment for endpoints (Desktops, laptops, servers etc.) using the following tools:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;SCCM 2016&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Intune&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Microsoft Endpoint Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Active Directory&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Group Policy&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Evidian (SSO) Single Sign On&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;System Center Endpoint Protection&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post is full time. Primarily based in Winchester, you will also be required to work at other HHFT sites at Basingstoke and Andover as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Marc Scanlon - Server Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;marc.scanlon@hhft.nhs.uk / 01962825996&lt;/p&gt;
